fields.descriptive_line: A set of 44 leg rings used by both men and women of one of the hill tribes of Kachin State northern Burma. Black thitsi lacquered bamboo. c. early 20th century.
fields.physical_description: Set of 44  bamboo leg rings used by both men and women of one of  the hill tribes of Kachin State, Northern Burma, as leg decorations just below the knee above their leggings. Finished with black thitsi lacquer.
fields.materials_techniques: Bamboo. Dye. Thitsi lacquer. Shaping. Lacquering. Dyeing.

fields.name: South and South East Asian Collection

fields.history_note: Such rings were used by both men and women as leg decoration just below the knee above their leggings.
